573
01:51:58,962 --> 01:52:00,172
Kelly, uh...

574
01:52:03,592 --> 01:52:05,302
She's had it rough.

575
01:52:05,469 --> 01:52:09,765
First when she thought she lost you,
now dealing with all of this.

576
01:52:09,973 --> 01:52:11,225
It's confusing.

577
01:52:11,433 --> 01:52:14,269
It's very emotional for her. She's...

578
01:52:17,356 --> 01:52:18,357
She's

579
01:52:19,733 --> 01:52:21,318
sort of lost.

580
01:52:23,320 --> 01:52:25,614
Maybe you could just
give her a little more time.

581
01:52:31,161 --> 01:52:32,162
Anyway...

582
01:52:33,705 --> 01:52:35,332
I'm sorry that...

583
01:53:32,931 --> 01:53:34,683
Okay, people, let's go.

584
01:53:34,766 --> 01:53:36,893
Party's over. Let's go home.

585
01:53:37,519 --> 01:53:39,855
You're gonna have to
go down at the DMV.

586
01:53:40,355 --> 01:53:42,357
Okay, Maynard, let's go.
Chuck's had a big day.

587
01:53:42,441 --> 01:53:46,278
I have to brief him on his meetings
with the accountants and attorneys.

588
01:53:46,361 --> 01:53:48,655
I will see you bright and early
in the morning.

589
01:53:49,156 --> 01:53:52,075
Chuck, welcome home. We love you.

590
01:53:52,159 --> 01:53:53,660
Becca, I need to speak to you.

591
01:53:53,744 --> 01:53:57,039
Chuck, we gotta catch up
on some of that fishing, now.

592
01:53:57,247 --> 01:53:58,582
Take care.

593
01:54:01,835 --> 01:54:03,754
- Good night.
- Good night.

594
01:54:07,382 --> 01:54:09,426
You got everything you need?

595
01:54:09,509 --> 01:54:14,014
Okay. If you need anything, sign for it,
and I'll see you in the morning.

596
01:54:14,097 --> 01:54:17,100
Get some sleep.
We got another big day tomorrow.

597
01:54:17,184 --> 01:54:19,936
It takes a lot of paperwork
to bring back a man.

598
01:54:21,271 --> 01:54:22,773
Bring you back to life, man.

599
01:54:23,815 --> 01:54:25,692
- Bye, Chuck.
- Take care, now.

600
01:54:25,776 --> 01:54:26,860
Tomorrow.

601
01:54:26,943 --> 01:54:29,446
Tomorrow we're gonna
bring you back to life.

602
01:56:14,551 --> 01:56:16,219
How long are you gonna be, man?

603
01:56:18,555 --> 01:56:19,723
Well...

604
01:56:21,308 --> 01:56:24,060
- How long will that buy me?
- About ten minutes.

605
01:56:48,460 --> 01:56:49,794
I'm awake.

606
01:56:50,629 --> 01:56:52,631
I saw your taxi drive up.

607
01:56:55,175 --> 01:56:57,302
Get in here out of the rain.

608
01:57:04,100 --> 01:57:07,854
I saw you down at the hub today,
so I know you were down there.

609
01:57:27,123 --> 01:57:29,042
Let me get you a towel.

610
01:57:40,971 --> 01:57:42,472
They're sleeping.

611
01:57:46,643 --> 01:57:49,980
You'll come in,
I'll make you some coffee?

612
01:58:02,409 --> 01:58:04,077
It's a nice house.

613
01:58:04,160 --> 01:58:05,829
Yeah, we got a nice mortgage, too.

614
01:58:14,170 --> 01:58:15,922
What's your daughter's name?

615
01:58:17,007 --> 01:58:18,008
Katie.

616
01:58:19,634 --> 01:58:20,635
Katie.

617
01:58:24,848 --> 01:58:26,600
She's a beautiful little girl.

618
01:58:26,683 --> 01:58:27,976
She's a handful.

619
01:58:42,532 --> 01:58:44,242
Let me get one thing straight.

620
01:58:54,127 --> 01:58:57,505
We have a pro football team now,
but they're in Nashville?

621
01:59:03,011 --> 01:59:06,097
Umm, yeah. Oh, my God. Okay.

622
01:59:06,681 --> 01:59:08,058
They used to be in Houston.

623
01:59:08,600 --> 01:59:11,686
First they were the Otters,
and now they're the Titans.

624
01:59:12,395 --> 01:59:15,065
The Houston Otters
are the Tennessee Titans?

625
01:59:15,565 --> 01:59:18,401
Yeah. But that's not all.

626
01:59:19,027 --> 01:59:21,655
They went to the Super Bowl last year.

627
01:59:22,155 --> 01:59:24,824
- And I missed that.
- You would've died.

628
01:59:24,908 --> 01:59:28,828
They almost won by one yard.
One lousy yard, right at the end.

629
01:59:30,789 --> 01:59:34,167
I got whole milk, 2% and non-fat.

630
01:59:34,250 --> 01:59:37,295
I don't have any half-and-half,
and that's what you like.

631
01:59:37,796 --> 01:59:39,172
That'll do fine.

632
01:59:52,686 --> 01:59:54,938
What happened to you
becoming a professor?

633
01:59:57,565 --> 02:00:00,610
You're not Dr Kelly Frears-Lovett?

634
02:00:03,988 --> 02:00:04,989
When you, um...

635
02:00:06,491 --> 02:00:08,201
When your plane went down,

636
02:00:09,494 --> 02:00:12,038
everything just sort of got put on hold.

637
02:00:14,457 --> 02:00:16,793
I think about taking it up again, though.

638
02:00:29,139 --> 02:00:31,516
I came out here to give you this.

639
02:00:32,684 --> 02:00:34,436
Oh, my God.

640
02:00:36,855 --> 02:00:38,898
I'm sorry it doesn't work.

641
02:00:40,442 --> 02:00:42,819
And I, uh, I kept the picture.

642
02:00:44,446 --> 02:00:46,406
It was all faded anyway.

643
02:00:47,782 --> 02:00:49,993
I want you to have it. I gave it to you.

644
02:00:50,702 --> 02:00:53,997
That's a family heirloom
and it should stay in your family.

645
02:01:03,673 --> 02:01:07,177
That's everything I have
from when you went down to now.

646
02:01:08,762 --> 02:01:11,347
They said they never figured out
what caused the crash.

647
02:01:11,681 --> 02:01:15,226
Probably some mislabelled
hazardous material caught fire.

648
02:01:18,980 --> 02:01:21,191
So here's where that ship found you.

649
02:01:22,984 --> 02:01:25,361
You drifted about 500 miles.

650
02:01:26,362 --> 02:01:28,490
This is where your island was,

651
02:01:28,698 --> 02:01:31,701
about 600 miles
south of the Cook Islands.

652
02:01:33,495 --> 02:01:35,747
And these are the search grids.

653
02:01:35,830 --> 02:01:39,167
Ships went back and forth
for weeks looking for you.

654
02:01:47,467 --> 02:01:50,178
I never should've gotten on that plane.

655
02:01:52,096 --> 02:01:54,349
I never should've gotten out of the car.

656
02:01:58,478 --> 02:02:00,438
I wanna show you something.

657
02:02:02,524 --> 02:02:03,691
Come here.

658
02:02:13,952 --> 02:02:16,079
This is... This is our car.

659
02:02:18,414 --> 02:02:20,375
You kept our car.

660
02:02:22,544 --> 02:02:24,546
All right, now...

661
02:02:25,004 --> 02:02:26,506
This is weird.

662
02:02:34,264 --> 02:02:35,807
It's a good car.

663
02:02:36,432 --> 02:02:38,852
Had a lot of memories in this car.

664
02:02:38,935 --> 02:02:40,728
Two very nice memories.

665
02:02:41,604 --> 02:02:44,232
Oh, that trip down to the Gulf, yeah.

666
02:02:46,234 --> 02:02:47,944
So, can I drive it?

667
02:02:48,361 --> 02:02:49,904
It's your car.

668
02:02:58,037 --> 02:03:00,999
That's good, 'cause my...
My taxi's gone.

669
02:03:07,171 --> 02:03:08,214
Um...

670
02:03:09,591 --> 02:03:11,843
Let me get some stuff out of the back.

671
02:03:34,073 --> 02:03:36,576
You think you're gonna have more kids?

672
02:03:36,659 --> 02:03:37,994
I don't know.

673
02:03:38,328 --> 02:03:40,747
It's kind of confusing right now.

674
02:03:41,623 --> 02:03:42,999
Well, you should.

675
02:03:44,167 --> 02:03:46,419
I mean, really, you should.

676
02:03:48,671 --> 02:03:49,672
I would.

677
02:03:52,675 --> 02:03:54,302
So, what now?

678
02:03:57,722 --> 02:03:59,182
I don't know.

679
02:04:02,268 --> 02:04:04,020
I really don't know.

680
02:04:16,699 --> 02:04:18,701
You said you'd be right back.

681
02:04:23,957 --> 02:04:25,750
I'm so sorry.

682
02:04:27,794 --> 02:04:29,003
Me, too.

683
02:05:39,115 --> 02:05:40,116
Chuck!

684
02:05:44,662 --> 02:05:45,705
Chuck!

685
02:05:47,290 --> 02:05:48,583
Chuck!

686
02:06:07,226 --> 02:06:09,437
I always knew you were alive.
I knew it.

687
02:06:11,189 --> 02:06:13,232
But everybody said
I had to stop saying that,

688
02:06:13,316 --> 02:06:14,692
that I had to let you go.

689
02:06:16,819 --> 02:06:18,196
I love you.

690
02:06:20,114 --> 02:06:22,158
You're the love of my life.

691
02:06:24,327 --> 02:06:26,120
I love you, too, Kelly.

692
02:06:28,247 --> 02:06:29,832
More than you'll ever know.

693
02:07:30,768 --> 02:07:31,769
Chuck?

694
02:07:39,652 --> 02:07:41,404
You have to go home.

695
02:08:30,786 --> 02:08:36,542
We both had done the math,
and Kelly added it all up.

696
02:08:39,295 --> 02:08:41,047
She knew she had to let me go.

697
02:08:41,130 --> 02:08:43,799
I added it up, knew that I'd...

698
02:08:45,676 --> 02:08:46,844
I'd lost her.

699
02:08:49,597 --> 02:08:52,391
'Cause I was never gonna
get off that island.

700
02:08:54,644 --> 02:08:58,481
I was gonna die there, totally alone.

701
02:09:05,571 --> 02:09:09,033
I mean, I was gonna get sick or
I was gonna get injured or something.

702
02:09:12,745 --> 02:09:14,622
The only choice I had,

703
02:09:17,333 --> 02:09:19,752
the only thing I could control

704
02:09:21,754 --> 02:09:24,131
was when and how

705
02:09:25,424 --> 02:09:28,135
and where
that was gonna happen. So...

706
02:09:30,471 --> 02:09:32,139
I made a rope.

707
02:09:34,850 --> 02:09:37,687
And I went up to the summit
to hang myself.

708
02:09:41,357 --> 02:09:43,359
But I had to test it, you know?

709
02:09:43,442 --> 02:09:45,861
Of course. You know me.

710
02:09:48,572 --> 02:09:53,703
And the weight of the log
snapped the limb of the tree.

711
02:09:53,828 --> 02:09:58,291
So I couldn't even kill myself
the way I wanted to.

712
02:09:58,374 --> 02:10:01,168
I had power over nothing.

713
02:10:10,011 --> 02:10:13,597
And that's when this feeling came
over me like a warm blanket.

714
02:10:17,643 --> 02:10:20,396
I knew, somehow,

715
02:10:22,189 --> 02:10:24,525
that I had to stay alive.

716
02:10:25,901 --> 02:10:27,236
Somehow.

717
02:10:28,946 --> 02:10:31,240
I had to keep breathing,

718
02:10:33,826 --> 02:10:36,579
even though
there was no reason to hope.

719
02:10:37,997 --> 02:10:41,667
And all my logic said that
I would never see this place again.

720
02:10:46,589 --> 02:10:48,424
So that's what I did.

721
02:10:49,508 --> 02:10:50,968
I stayed alive.

722
02:10:52,136 --> 02:10:53,888
I kept breathing.

723
02:10:56,349 --> 02:10:58,684
Then one day
that logic was proven all wrong,

724
02:10:58,768 --> 02:11:03,439
because the tide came in,

725
02:11:03,731 --> 02:11:05,608
gave me a sail.

726
02:11:09,904 --> 02:11:11,614
And now, here I am.

727
02:11:15,076 --> 02:11:19,163
I'm back in Memphis,

728
02:11:19,372 --> 02:11:21,290
talking to you.

729
02:11:22,875 --> 02:11:24,794
I have ice in my glass.

730
02:11:32,009 --> 02:11:34,387
And I've lost her all over again.

731
02:11:42,228 --> 02:11:44,688
I'm so sad that I don't have Kelly.

732
02:11:49,902 --> 02:11:53,739
But I'm so grateful that
she was with me on that island.

733
02:12:00,287 --> 02:12:02,832
And I know what I have to do now.

734
02:12:05,584 --> 02:12:07,503
I gotta keep breathing.

735
02:12:10,172 --> 02:12:12,675
Because tomorrow, the sun will rise.

736
02:12:13,843 --> 02:12:16,095
Who knows what the tide could bring?

737
02:13:22,161 --> 02:13:23,329
Hello!

738
02:13:28,375 --> 02:13:29,376
Hello!

739
02:13:38,052 --> 02:13:39,220
FedEx!

740
02:14:47,830 --> 02:14:49,081
You look lost.

741
02:14:49,582 --> 02:14:50,583
I do?

742
02:14:51,625 --> 02:14:53,002
Where are you headed?

743
02:14:57,047 --> 02:14:58,924
Well, I was just about to figure that out.

744
02:15:00,509 --> 02:15:01,885
Well, that's 83 South.

745
02:15:02,678 --> 02:15:05,806
And this road here will hook you up
with I-40 East.

746
02:15:07,349 --> 02:15:10,936
If you turn right, that'll take you to

747
02:15:11,020 --> 02:15:14,565
Amarillo, Flagstaff, California.

748
02:15:17,151 --> 02:15:19,778
And if you head back that direction,
you'll find a whole lot of nothing

749
02:15:19,862 --> 02:15:21,614
all the way to Canada.

750
02:15:24,283 --> 02:15:25,534
I got it.

751
02:15:26,160 --> 02:15:27,536
All right, then.

752
02:15:30,539 --> 02:15:32,041
Good luck, cowboy.

753
02:15:32,791 --> 02:15:33,917
Thank you.
